solutions.content:
- iterate all the words in the wordDict, find if the prefix of the current string matches a word in the dictionary
- current string = prefix + suffix
- if true, we do the same operation to the suffix, and find its list of word break ==> **sublist**
- return the final list of word break of the original string by concating **prefix + sublist**

The time complexity is O(len(wordDict) ^ len(s / minWordLenInDict)) 

```
class Solution {
    public List<String> wordBreak(String s, List<String> wordDict) {
        // dfs with memorization
        return dfs(s, wordDict, new HashMap<String, List<String>>());
    }

    private List<String> dfs(String s, List<String> wordDict, HashMap<String, List<String>> memo) {
        if (memo.containsKey(s)) return memo.get(s);

        List<String> res = new ArrayList<>();
        for (String word : wordDict) {
            if (s.startsWith(word)) {
                String next = s.substring(word.length());
                List<String> sublist = dfs(s.substring(word.length()), wordDict, memo);
                if (next.isEmpty()) res.add(word);
                else {
                    for(String sub: sublist) {
                        res.add(word + " " + sub);
                    }
                }            
            }
        } 
        memo.put(s, res);
        return res;
    }
}
```

