**Approach:**
1. We will start iterate from m[0][m] or m[n][0]   where m = no. of colums and n =no. of rows.
2. then we have have left element is always smaller and down element is bigger then current in whole matrix (Given rows are sorted).
3. Then we will loop from` (r < row && r >=0)` and ` (c < col && c >= 0)` this prevent overflow.
4. Then if current element is smaller then will we go down ( `r++;` ).
5. Then if current element is bigger then will we go left ( `c--;` ).
6. If element found we will return true else false.



```
class Solution {
public:
    bool searchMatrix(vector<vector<int>>& matrix, int target) {

        int row = matrix.size();
        int col = matrix[0].size();

        int c = col-1;
        int r =0;
        while((r < row && r >=0)  && (c < col && c >= 0)){

            int element = matrix[r][c];

            if(element == target){
                return true;
            }
             else if(element > target){
                  c--;
            }else{
                 r++;
             }
        }
        return false;

    }
};
```

