# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The given problem asks to find whether an element is present in a matrix or not. Since the matrix is sorted, we can use binary search to solve this problem. To perform binary search, we can search each row of the matrix using binary search. If we find the target element in any row, we return true, otherwise, we return false.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

We iterate over each row of the matrix using a for loop

For each row, we perform binary search by initializing two pointers l and r with the start and end indices of the row, respectively.

We repeat the following until l<=r:

a. We calculate the middle index of the row by using the formula mid=l+(r-l)/2.
b. If the element at the middle index is equal to the target element, we return true.
c. If the element at the middle index is less than the target element, we update l to mid+1.
d. If the element at the middle index is greater than the target element, we update r to mid-1.

If we do not find the target element in any row, we return false.
# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(mlog(n))$$, where m is the number of rows and n is the number of columns of the matrix. For each row, we perform binary search which takes log(n) time, so the total time complexity is O(mlog(n))
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$, as we are using constant extra space
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool searchMatrix(vector<vector<int>>& matrix, int target) {
        int m=matrix.size();
        int n=matrix[0].size();

        for(int i=0; i<m ; i++)
        {
        int l=0;
        int r=n-1;
        while(l<=r)
           {
                int mid=l + (r-l)/2;
                if (matrix[i][mid] == target) return true;
                if (matrix[i][mid] < target)
                {
                    l=mid+1;
                }
                else 
                {
                    r=mid-1; 
                }
            }

        }
         return false;
    }
};
```

