We start in the bottom-left corner, which is 
matrix[-1][0]. Obviously, the target cell cannot
be either below or to the left of this corner cell

• We move incrementally from the corner such that we 
do not pass to right of the target's column or above
its row; we can ensure this by exploiting the sorted 
rows and columns. For example (below), the target 
is 8 and and the corner is 18. So:
      -- 18 > 8 =>  move up    to 10,
      -- 10 > 8 =>  move up    to  3,
      --  3 < 8 =>  move right to  6,
      --  6 < 8 =>  move right to  9,
      --  9 > 8 =>  move up    to  8.
