Use binary search. It mid is even, then check nums[mid] and nums[mid + 1]. If they are equal, then the target must be on the right half. Similarly for mid is odd, check nums[mid] and nums[mid - 1].
```
class Solution(object):
    def singleNonDuplicate(self, nums):
        """
        :type nums: List[int]
        :rtype: int
        """
        left, right = 0, len(nums) - 1
        while left + 1 < right:
            mid = (left + right) // 2
            if mid % 2 == 1:
                if nums[mid] == nums[mid - 1]:
                    left = mid
                else:
                    right = mid
            else:
                if nums[mid] == nums[mid + 1]:
                    left = mid
                else:
                    right = mid
        #print(left, right)
        if left % 2 == 0:
            return nums[left]
        return nums[right]
```
