# Code JAVA
```
class Solution {
    public int singleNonDuplicate(int[] nums) {
        int n = nums.length;
        int l = 0;
        int r = n-1;

        if(n==1)
            return nums[0];
        if(nums[0] != nums[1])
            return nums[0];
        if(nums[n-1] != nums[n-2])
            return nums[n-1];

        while(l<=r){
            int mid = l+(r-l)/2;

            if(mid>0 && mid < n-1){
                if(nums[mid] > nums[mid-1] && nums[mid] < nums[mid+1])
                    return nums[mid];
                else if((nums[mid] == nums[mid-1] && mid%2==1) || (nums[mid] == nums[mid+1] && mid%2==0))
                    l = mid+1;
                else 
                    r = mid -1;
            }
        }
        return 0;
    }
}
```

