**Approach 1**: Bit manupulation - TC O(n) - SC (1)
Here we use the fact that performing XOR with two same numbers give us zero and doing XOR with zero and other number will give us that number itself.
here's the example
2 - 0010
2 - 0010
3 - 0011

So 2^2^3 = 3

So we simply iterate through the loop and do XOR and the final ans will be the required ans
**Approach 2**:HashMap
We use an HashMap to make a frequency table to note number of occurrences of the elements.
Then we use an Entry Set to iterate and return the element with the single occurrence.


